of%20a%20structure%20start%20to%20crack%2C%20how%20long%20can%20the%20roof%20hold%20up%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Union%20In%20Crisis%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union%2C%20built%20on%20the%20lofty%20ideals%20of%20democracy%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20now%20finds%20itself%20teetering%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20an%20existential%20crisis.%20The%20irony%20is%20as%20rich%20as%20it%20is%20tragic%3A%20a%20union%20founded%20on%20unity%20is%20fracturing%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20its%20contradictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20start%20with%20the%20obvious.%20Britain%20exited%20the%20Union%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20alone.%20In%20France%2C%20Marine%20Le%20Pen%20lurks%20menacingly%20in%20the%20political%20shadows%2C%20her%20far-right%20populism%20offering%20voters%20a%20seductive%2C%20anti-EU%20narrative.%20In%20Italy%2C%20Matteo%20Salvini%20champions%20a%20similar%20brand%20of%20nationalist%20fervour%2C%20while%20in%20Germany%2C%20the%20far-right%20AfD%20party%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20fringe%20player%20but%20a%20rising%20force%20to%20be%20reckoned%20with.%20The%20EU%20isn't%20just%20rotting%20from%20outside%E2%80%94it%20is%20under%20siege%20from%20within.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Europhiles%20Play%20The%20Populist%20Card%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoland's%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Donald%20Tusk%2C%20is%20a%20known%20Europhile.%20But%20it%20was%20shocking%20for%20many%20in%20the%20EU%20that%20he%20suspended%20the%20right%20to%20asylum%20in%20his%20country%2C%20putting%20aside%20the%20bloc's%20own%20principles.%20Tusk%20was%20a%20man%20who%20spent%20years%20championing%20European%20values%2C%20and%20now%20he%20undermines%20one%20of%20their%20cornerstones%2C%20all%20to%20save%20his%20own%20skin.%20Cynically%2C%20he%20justified%20his%20decision%20by%20saying%20that%20Russia%20and%20Belarus%20were%20diverting%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20his%20country%20and%20other%20EU%20member%20countries%2C%20a%20charge%20still%20unproven.%20But%20his%20critics%20point%20out%20that%20his%20real%20worries%20are%20a%20lot%20closer%20to%20home.%20His%20pro-EU%20Civic%20Platform%20coalition%20may%20have%20scraped%20through%20Poland's%20parliamentary%20elections%20last%20year%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20floundering%20ever%20since.%20Polls%20now%20show%20Tusk's%20party%20neck%20and%20neck%20with%20the%20Eurosceptic%20Law%20and%20Justice%20Party%20(PiS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETusk%20is%20not%20alone.%20Struggling%20Europhile%20leaders%20across%20the%20continent%20are%20suddenly%20discovering%20the%20political%20utility%20of%20%26quot%3Bsecuring%20national%20borders%26quot%3B.%20Take%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Olaf%20Scholz%2C%20Germany's%20embattled%20chancellor.%20His%20popularity%20is%20sinking%20fast.%20Recently%2C%20Scholz%20imposed%20border%20controls%20across%20all%20of%20Germany's%20land%20borders%2C%20citing%20an%20Islamist%20terror%20attack%20in%20Solingen%20as%20the%20trigger.%20But%20let's%20call%20it%20what%20it%20is%3A%20a%20calculated%20move%20for%20the%20February%20election%20to%20placate%20voters%20fed%20up%20with%20migration%20and%20to%20fend%20off%20rising%20populist%20parties%20like%20the%20AfD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDouble%20Standards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20Brussels%20itself%E2%80%94the%20hallowed%20guardian%20of%20European%20unity%2C%20democracy%20and%20human%20rights.%20It%20has%20made%20a%20remarkable%20U-turn%20on%20migration.%20Recently%2C%20after%20one%20of%20its%20signature%20closed-door%20meetings%2C%20the%20European%20Commission%20threw%20its%20weight%20behind%20Tusk.%20In%20a%20statement%20backed%20by%20all%2027%20member%20states%2C%20Brussels%20claimed%20that%20Russia%20and%20Belarus%20are%20%E2%80%9Cabusing%20our%20values%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cundermining%20our%20democracies%E2%80%9D.%20It%20justified%20its%20stance%20by%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cexceptional%20situations%20require%20appropriate%20measures%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApparently%2C%20the%20EU%20has%20decided%20that%20border%20controls%20are%20acceptable%20so%20long%20as%20the%20justification%20is%20wrapped%20in%20anti-Russian%20rhetoric%20and%20presented%20by%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20leader.%20To%20understand%20the%20EU's%20hypocrisy%2C%20let's%20remind%20ourselves%20what%20it%20did%20to%20Viktor%20Orb%C3%A1n's%20Hungary%E2%80%94Orb%C3%A1n%20being%20a%20%E2%80%98bad%20boy'%20of%20Europe%20for%20supporting%20Russia.%20Recently%2C%20the%20EU's%20top%20court%20fined%20Hungary%20%E2%82%AC200m%20for%20failing%20to%20follow%20the%20union's%20asylum%20policies.%20The%20court%20will%20also%20issue%20a%20penalty%20of%20%E2%82%AC1m%20a%20day%20until%20it%20changes%20its%20policy.%20The%20European%20Court%20of%20Justice%20said%20Budapest%20was%20in%20breach%20of%20a%202020%20judgement%20and%20had%20violated%20EU%20laws%20by%20forcing%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20travel%20to%20Belgrade%20or%20Kyiv%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20travel%20permit%20for%20entering%20Hungary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20double%20standards%20are%20impossible%20to%20ignore.%20When%20Poland's%20PiS%20government%20previously%20clamped%20down%20on%20migration%2C%20Brussels%20was%20quick%20to%20condemn%20it%20as%20a%20betrayal%20of%20European%20values.%20But%20now%20that%20Tusk%20is%20doing%20the%20same%2C%20suddenly%2C%20the%20EU%20is%20all%20right%20with%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrance%20Faces%20People's%20Mistrust%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Macron%20and%20France's%20so-called%20political%20class%20are%20facing%20a%20sea%20of%20public%20mistrust.%20A%20recent%20Le%20Monde%20survey%20paints%20a%20grim%20picture%3A%20only%2022%25%20of%20French%20people%20trust%20their%20MPs%E2%80%94a%20seven-point%20drop%20in%20just%20a%20year.%20Voters%20are%20sick%20of%20the%20endless%20political%20bickering.%20And%20who%20can%20blame%20them%3F%20With%20faith%20in%20the%20system%20evaporating%2C%20the%20odds%20that%20fresh%20parliamentary%20elections%20next%20summer%20will%20magically%20deliver%20a%20stable%20majority%20seem%20very%20slim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20timing%20couldn't%20be%20worse.%20The%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20at%20a%20potential%20turning%20point%2C%20and%20across%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20a%20new%20Trump%20administration%20looms%2C%20itching%20to%20kickstart%20a%20trade%20war%20that%20could%20send%20shockwaves%20through%20Europe's%20fragile%20economy.%20For%20now%2C%20Macron%20still%20holds%20the%20reins%E2%80%94at%20least%20on%20paper.%20But%20he%20has%20to%20convince%20France's%20allies%20that%20the%20nation%20isn't%20about%20to%20unravel%20completely.%20With%20domestic%20gridlock%20and%20global%20crises%20closing%20in%2C%20it's%20up%20to%20him%20to%20prove%20that%20France%20can%20still%20play%20ball%20on%20the%20world%20stage.%20The%20question%20is%3A%20does%20anyone%20still%20believe%20he%20can%20pull%20it%20off%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUkraine%20Obsession%3A%20A%20Crisis%20Of%20Priorities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union%20is%20pouring%20billions%20into%20Ukraine%E2%80%94defence%20aid%2C%20financial%20packages%2C%20reconstruction%20pledges%E2%80%94all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20standing%20up%20to%20Russian%20aggression.%20But%20its%20own%20citizens%20are%20buckling%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20spiralling%20costs.%20Energy%20bills%20are%20sky-high%2C%20inflation%20continues%20to%20bite%20and%20wages%20remain%20stagnant.%20Let's%20be%20blunt%2C%20I%20live%20and%20travel%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Europe%20and%20I%20feel%20it%3A%20the%20EU's%20relentless%20commitment%20to%20Ukraine%20isn't%20just%20draining%20its%20coffers%2C%20it's%20bleeding%20its%20people%20dry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%2C%20ever%20the%20puppet%20master%2C%20has%20pulled%20the%20EU%20deep%20into%20the%20Ukrainian%20quagmire.%20Washington's%20playbook%20is%20clear%3A%20keep%20Europe%20committed%20to%20Ukraine%20as%20a%20frontline%20bulwark%20against%20Russia.%20But%20what%20has%20Europe%20gained%3F%20Endless%20sanctions%20that%20hurt%20its%20own%20economies%20more%20than%20Moscow's%2C%20and%20a%20cold%20winter%20of%20discontent%20driven%20by%20an%20overreliance%20on%20expensive%20LNG%20imports%20from%20across%20the%20Atlantic.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Russia%2C%20as%20I%20have%20said%20in%20my%20previous%20columns%2C%20though%20battered%2C%20is%20far%20from%20broken.%20Its%20economy%20is%20adapting%20and%20its%20territorial%20grip%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%20remains%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20Awkward%20Dance%20With%20Trump%20And%20Musk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEurope's%20love%20affair%20with%20the%20American%20tech%20and%20political%20elite%20has%20soured%20spectacularly.%20Donald%20Trump's%20triumphant%20return%20and%20his%20bromance%20with%20Elon%20Musk%20may%20spell%20trouble%20for%20the%20EU's%20ambitious%20tech%20crackdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20talk%20about%20X%2C%20Musk's%20digital%20playground%2C%20and%20its%20showdown%20with%20the%20EU's%20Digital%20Services%20Act%20(DSA).%20This%20isn't%20just%20another%20slap-on-the-wrist%20regulation.%20Passed%20in%202022%2C%20the%20DSA%20packs%20a%20punch%2C%20demanding%20platforms%20remove%20illegal%20content%20or%20face%20fines%20of%20up%20to%206%25%20of%20their%20annual%20revenue.%20Musk's%20X%20is%20on%20the%20radar%20of%20the%20EU%20regulators%2C%20who%20have%20alleged%20multiple%20violations%20of%20the%20DSA%20rules.%20Now%2C%20they're%20mulling%20their%20next%20move%E2%80%94fine%20X%2C%20slap%20Musk%20with%20penalties%2C%20or%20go%20after%20both.%20But%20that%20was%20before%20Trump%20was%20in%20play.%20Now%20that%20he%20is%2C%20the%20EU's%20tech%20crusade%20is%20about%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20messier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDigital%20Dinosaur%20In%20A%20World%20Of%20Tech%20Titans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20EU's%20biggest%20problems%20is%20that%20it's%20not%20disintegrating%E2%80%94it's%20badly%20stagnating.%20Former%20Italian%20Prime%20Minister%20Mario%20Draghi%20sounded%20the%20alarm%20in%20September.%20In%20his%20much-anticipated%20328-page%20report%2C%20Draghi%20pulled%20no%20punches%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20an%20existential%20challenge%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Europe%20needs%20to%20raise%20its%20annual%20investment%20by%20a%20staggering%20%E2%82%AC800%20billion%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20with%20much%20of%20that%20going%20to%20tech.%20Without%20it%2C%20the%20continent%20risks%20being%20left%20in%20the%20dust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeattle-based%2C%20Indian-origin%20tech%20expert%20S.%20Aamir%20Aarfi%20says%20that%20Europe%20needs%20to%20act%20fast%2C%20as%20it%20currently%20lags%20behind%20all%20the%20top%20players.%20Says%20he%2C%20%26quot%3BSilicon%20Valley%20churns%20out%20innovation%20at%20warp%20speed%2C%20China%20dominates%20AI%20and%205G%2C%20and%20even%20India%20is%20emerging%20as%20a%20tech%20powerhouse.%20Unfortunately%2C%20Europe%20clings%20to%20regulations%20and%20bureaucracy%2C%20dangerously%20close%20to%20stagnation%20and%20irrelevance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsider%20the%20cold%2C%20hard%20facts%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Aarfi%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20US%20dominates%20Big%20Tech%20and%20is%20home%20to%20giants%20like%20Apple%2C%20Google%20and%20Microsoft.%20China%20has%20its%20state-backed%20juggernauts%E2%80%94Tencent%2C%20Alibaba%2C%20and%20Huawei.%20But%20Europe%3F%20It%20boasts%20only%20the%20SAP%26quot%3B.%20Draghi%20notes%20that%20a%20mere%20four%20of%20the%20world's%20top%2050%20tech%20companies%20are%20European.%20He%20doesn't%20mince%20words%3A%20%26quot%3BEurope%20largely%20missed%20out%20on%20the%20digital%20revolution%20led%20by%20the%20internet%20and%20the%20productivity%20gains%20it%20brought.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EU%20appears%20to%20be%20spending%20more%20time%20regulating%20than%20innovating.%20Its%20flagship%20Digital%20Services%20and%20Markets%20Acts%20are%20more%20about%20policing%20foreign%20tech%20than%20fostering%20local%20growth.%20Meanwhile%2C%20European%20startups%20struggle%20to%20scale%2C%20stifled%20by%20red%20tape%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20venture%20capital.%20Europe%20dithers%20over%20ethics%2C%20while%20its%20brightest%20minds%20head%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%20or%20Shenzhen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDraghi's%20diagnosis%20is%20clear%3A%20Europe%20isn't%20just%20falling%20behind%E2%80%94it's%20failing%20to%20show%20up.%20If%20it%20doesn't%20act%20boldly%20and%20invest%20massively%2C%20it%20risks%20becoming%20a%20digital%20backwater%2C%20sidelined%20in%20the%20industries%20defining%20the%20future.%20As%20Aarfi%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BEurope%20needs%20a%20tech%20revolution%20and%20it%20needs%20it%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20greatest%20threat%20to%20the%20EU%20doesn't%20come%20from%20Moscow%20or%20Beijing%20but%20from%20within.%20Populist%20and%20nationalist%20movements%20are%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20fuelled%20by%20a%20toxic%20blend%20of%20economic%20anxiety%2C%20cultural%20insecurity%2C%20and%20distrust%20of%20Brussels.%20Stuck%20in%20a%20web%20of%20noble%20intentions%20but%20shoddy%20execution%2C%20the%20EU%20risks%20becoming%20irrelevant%E2%80%94not%20through%20dramatic%20collapse%2C%20but%20through%20a%20slow%2C%20self-inflicted%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733751240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-06%2Fbritish-with-eu-flag-reuters_650x400_51466763676.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ffrance-to-germany-to-belgium-the-eu-is-withering-away-7208998%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20greatest%20threat%20to%20the%20EU%2